    "<em>Rediscoveries in Art</em> (1976) established Oxford's Art History Department as the center of French Salon study and Parisian art market criticism.": [],
    "A number of other books--always different from the last--followed.": [],
    "<em>Taste and the Antique</em> (1981), co-authored by <a href=\"/pennyn\">Nicholas Penny</a>, traces how taste was transformed by the discovery of classical sculpture in 18th-century gardens by travelers, and the concomitant development of museums.": [],
    "Haskell remained at Oxford until his retirement in 1995.": [],
    "A pronouncedly modest and retiring personality, his brilliant lecturing style was by most accounts assisted with the aid a shot of whiskey immediately before them.": [
